{"atom_id": "ig34_p0452_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 452, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§10.E Appendix E: Revision History", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Morphology (MO)", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.7", "ts": "2026-04-29T14:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0452_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 452, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§10.E Appendix E: Revision History", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "When the Morphology domain was introduced in SDTMIG v3.2, the SDS Team planned to represent morphology and physiology findings in separate domains: morphology findings in the MO domain and physiology findings in separate domains by body systems.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.7", "ts": "2026-04-29T14:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0452_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 452, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§10.E Appendix E: Revision History", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Since then, the team found that separating morphology and physiology findings was more difficult than anticipated and provided little added value.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.7", "ts": "2026-04-29T14:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0452_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 452, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§10.E Appendix E: Revision History", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This led to the decision to expand the body system-based domains to cover both morphology and physiology findings and to deprecate MO in SDTMIG v3.4.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.7", "ts": "2026-04-29T14:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0452_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 452, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§10.E Appendix E: Revision History", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "Submissions using that later SDTMIG version would represent morphology results in the appropriate body system-based physiology/morphology domain.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.7", "ts": "2026-04-29T14:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0452_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 452, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§10.E Appendix E: Revision History", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "For data prepared using a version of the SDTMIG that includes both the MO domain and body system-based physiology/morphology domains, morphology findings may be represented in either the MO domain or in a body-system based physiology/morphology domain.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.7", "ts": "2026-04-29T14:00:00Z"}}
