{"atom_id": "ig34_p0455_a011", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 455, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§10.E Appendix E: Revision History", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "6.2.1 | Adverse Events (AE) | New AE variables for Medical Devices were added: SPDEVID, AEACNDEV, AEUNANT, AERLPRC, AERLPRT, AERLDEV, AESINTV. New Examples 5 and 6 were added to show examples of the new AE variables. We have deleted AE Assumption 2e as this was superseded by the addition of MedDRA coding variables in Amendment 1 to SDTMIG v3.1.2 and SDTM v1.2. Assumption 6, Actions taken, was added.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.7", "ts": "2026-04-29T14:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0455_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 455, "page_region": "bottom", "parent_section": "§10.E Appendix E: Revision History", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "6.2.2 | Biospecimen Events (BE) | This specification, assumptions, and examples were copied from the SDTMIG-PGx, published 2015-05-26, the BETERM and BEDECOD have been updated. PF has also been updated to GF. SDTMIG-PGx, originally published 2015-05-26, is to be deprecated with the publication of SDTMIG v3.4.", "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:executor", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.7", "ts": "2026-04-29T14:00:00Z"}}
